JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South African retailer and wholesaler Spar Group has closed its distribution centre in Zimbabwe due to weak economic growth and will now supply independent stores from South Africa, the firm&#8217;s chief executive said on Wednesday.&#8220;The economy was just too tough&#8230; payment issues, infrastructure issues, so it was better that we exited,&#8221; Spar Group chief executive Graham O&#8217;Connor told Reuters. 